transcript.name: t1
transcript.comment: This transcript is identical to the RefSeq transcript NM_002111.8 but with the polyA tail removed.

There is a difference in the coding sequence of this transcript with respect to Ensembl transcript ENST00000355072.9. ENST00000355072.9 matches the Primary Genome Assembly and contains 19 CAG repeats, LRG_763_t1/NM_002111.8 has 21 CAG repeats. The two transcript models (ENST00000355072 and NM_002111.8) are otherwise the same.
There is a difference(s) in the coding sequence of this transcript with respect to the Primary Genome Assembly (GRCh38). See the sequence difference(s)

annotation_set.note:
In the general population there is variation in the number of CAG repeats (9 - 35 repeats) in the HTT coding region (the expansion of this region to >= 36 repeats results in Huntington disease).
The Primary Genome Reference Assembly (GRCh37/38) contains 19 CAG repeats (referred to as 21Q due to the presence of other Q-encoding codons). The LRG sequences (RefSeq Gene NG_009378.1, transcript NM_002111.8 and protein NP_002102.4) represent 21 CAG repeats (referred to as 23Q).
The LRG sequences are those most commonly used by the clinical and research communitites. Both repeat numbers are similarly represented in the general population and neither is associated with Huntington Disease.
